changeMainAuthorizer(address).custom:event: MainAuthorizerChanged Emitted when the main authorizer address changes.
changeMainAuthorizer(address).custom:require: Only the owner can change the main authorizer address.The new main authorizer address cannot be zero.The new main authorizer address cannot be the same as the current main authorizer.

params.newMainAuthorizer: The address of the new main authorizer.

computeSignedMsg(string,string,bytes32).details: This function is used internally to generate the message that needs to be signed for setting or revoking a public key hash.

params.domainName: The domain name related to the operation.
params.publicKeyHash: The DKIM public key hash involved in the operation.

params._initialOwner: The address of the initial owner of the contract.
params._mainAuthorizer: The address of the main authorizer.
params._setTimestampDelay: The time delay until a DKIM public key hash set by the main authorizer is enabled.

isDKIMPublicKeyHashValid(string,bytes32).details: This function returns true if the owner of the given `msg.sender` approves the public key hash before `enabledTimeOfDKIMPublicKeyHash` and neither `mainAuthorizer` nor the owner of `msg.sender` revokes the public key hash. However, after `enabledTimeOfDKIMPublicKeyHash`, only one of their approvals is required. In addition, if the public key hash is reactivated by the owner of `msg.sender`, the public key hash revoked only by `mainAuthorizer` is considered valid.

params.domainName: The domain name for which the DKIM public key hash is being checked.
params.publicKeyHash: The hash of the DKIM public key to be checked.

returns._0: bool True if the DKIM public key hash is valid, false otherwise.

isDKIMPublicKeyHashValid(string,bytes32,.details: This function returns true if 1) at least the given `authorizer` approves the public key hash before `enabledTimeOfDKIMPublicKeyHash` and 2) neither `mainAuthorizer` nor `authorizer` revokes the public key hash. However, after `enabledTimeOfDKIMPublicKeyHash`, only one of their approvals is required. In addition, if the public key hash is reactivated by the `authorizer`, the public key hash revoked only by `mainAuthorizer` is considered valid.The domain name, public key hash, and authorizer address must not be zero.The authorizer address cannot be the mainAuthorizer.

params.authorizer: The address of the expected authorizer
params.domainName: The domain name for which the DKIM public key hash is being checked.
params.publicKeyHash: The hash of the DKIM public key to be checked.

returns._0: bool True if the DKIM public key hash is valid, false otherwise.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

reactivateDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes.custom:event: DKIMPublicKeyHashReactivated Emitted when a DKIM public key hash is successfully reactivated.
reactivateDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes.custom:require: The domain name, public key hash, and authorizer address must not be zero.The public key hash must be revoked by the main authorizer.The signature must be valid according to EIP-1271 if the authorizer is a contract, or ECDSA if the authorizer is an EOA.
reactivateDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes.details: This function allows an authorized user or a contract to reactivate a DKIM public key hash that was revoked by the main authorizer.

params.authorizer: The address of the authorizer who can reactivate the DKIM public key hash.
params.domainName: The domain name associated with the DKIM public key hash.
params.publicKeyHash: The hash of the DKIM public key to be reactivated.
params.signature: The signature proving the authorization to reactivate the DKIM public key hash.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

revokeDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,a.custom:event: DKIMPublicKeyHashRevoked Emitted when a DKIM public key hash is successfully revoked.
revokeDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,a.custom:require: The domain name, public key hash, and authorizer address must not be zero.The public key hash must not already be revoked.The signature must be valid according to EIP-1271 if the authorizer is a contract, or ECDSA if the authorizer is an EOA.
revokeDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,a.details: This function allows the owner to revoke a DKIM public key hash for all users, or an individual user to revoke it for themselves.

params.authorizer: The address of the authorizer who can revoke the DKIM public key hash.
params.domainName: The domain name associated with the DKIM public key hash.
params.publicKeyHash: The hash of the DKIM public key to be revoked.
params.signature: The signature proving the authorization to revoke the DKIM public key hash.

setDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,addr.custom:event: DKIMPublicKeyHashRegistered Emitted when a DKIM public key hash is successfully set.
setDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,addr.custom:require: The domain name, public key hash, and authorizer address must not be zero.The public key hash must not be revoked.The signature must be valid according to EIP-1271 if the authorizer is a contract, or ECDSA if the authorizer is an EOA.
setDKIMPublicKeyHash(string,bytes32,addr.details: This function allows an authorized user or a contract to set a DKIM public key hash. It uses EIP-1271 or ECDSA for signature verification.

params.authorizer: The address of the authorizer who can set the DKIM public key hash.
params.domainName: The domain name for which the DKIM public key hash is being set.
params.publicKeyHash: The hash of the DKIM public key to be set.
params.signature: The signature proving the authorization to set the DKIM public key hash.

setDKIMPublicKeyHashes(string[],bytes32[.custom:event: DKIMPublicKeyHashRegistered Emitted when a DKIM public key hash is successfully set.
setDKIMPublicKeyHashes(string[],bytes32[.custom:require: The domain name, public key hash, and authorizer address must not be zero.The public key hash must not be revoked.The signature must be valid according to EIP-1271 if the authorizer is a contract, or ECDSA if the authorizer is an EOA.
setDKIMPublicKeyHashes(string[],bytes32[.details: Sets the DKIM public key hashes in batch.

params.authorizers: An array of the address of the authorizer who can set the DKIM public key hash.
params.domainNames: An array of the domain name for which the DKIM public key hash is being set.
params.publicKeyHashes: An array of the hash of the DKIM public key to be set.
params.signatures: An array of the signature proving the authorization to set the DKIM public key hash.
